# Secrets file — loaded at runtime, never seen by Docker Compose
#
# Copy to .env.secrets and fill in your values.
# This file is gitignored and MUST NOT be added to version control.
#
# Why a separate file?
#   Docker Compose resolves env_file variables into plaintext when running
#   `docker compose config`. VS Code's Dev Containers extension invokes this
#   command during container creation, which would expose secrets in logs.
#   Variables in .env.secrets are loaded by shell initialization scripts
#   at runtime instead, keeping them out of Docker Compose's output.
#
# Search order (first match wins):
#   1. $ENV_SECRETS_FILE  — explicit path override
#   2. $HOME/.env.secrets — user-level secrets
#   3. $PWD/.env.secrets  — project-level secrets (container WORKDIR)

# Required: Your 1Password service account token
# Get one at: https://developer.1password.com/docs/service-accounts/
#
# OP_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_TOKEN=ops_your_token_here
